==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Electrode
<hw>E*lec"trode</hw> <pr>(⟦esl⟧*l⟦ecr⟧k"tr⟦omac⟧d)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Electro-</ets> + Gr. <grk>"odo`s</grk> way, path: cf. F.
<ets>⟦eacute⟧lectrode</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Elec.)</fld> <def>a conducting
object by which electricity is conveyed into or from a solution or other
non-metallic conducting medium; esp., the ends of the wires or
conductors, leading from source of electricity, and terminating in the
medium traversed by the current.</def> <note>Electrodes may be specially
designed or made of a special material for particular purposes, as for
example silver <ex>electrodes</ex> used in electroplating.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

